This paper deals with adversarial machine learning, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several sub-fields in computer science. The paper proposes a new method for assessing the robustness of neural networks, which is relevant to the field of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also evaluates the robustness of several state-of-the-art models and defenses, which is relevant to computer vision (cs.CV) and cybersecurity (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the limitations of current metrics and proposes a new approach, which is relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.CR, cs.AI, and cs.NE, in that order.
